n<String>` field you added to `Message` variants has `#[serde(default)]`, so deserialization of old checkpoint JSONL files without that field is fully backward-compatible. And again, the Cursor DB parsing constructs `Message` objects manually from raw JSON values — it never round-trips through serde deserialization of your struct.\n\n**Where the messages DO go (when configured correctly):**\n- If you're logged in → messages are uploaded to CAS and a `messages_url` is set in the note\n- If you set `prompt_storage_mode = \"notes\"` in your config → messages go directly into the git note (with secret redaction)\n- If `prompt_storage_mode = \"local\"` → messages are stripped from notes but saved to your local SQLite DB (only if `checkpoint.transcript` is non-None)\n\nFor local development/testing without a login, set `prompt_storage_mode = \"local\"` or `\"notes\"` in your `~/.git-ai/config.toml` (or equivalent) to actually persist the messages.",
